Date:  21/3/1981
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  67
Edition:
Quote:  Ross prepared a "foot" to wedge into the base of the post ... The "foot" was a solid piece of totara with a length of No8 wire stapled to it.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1982
Source:  MAF Agricultural Glossary
Author:  MAF
Vol / Page:  28
Edition:
Quote:  Foot: a block of wood attached by wire to a post and buried with the post in a post-hole, or some other device to stop the post being pulled out when the fence is strained.
